<para0 verstatus="ver"><title>Use of "Shall", "Will", "Should", and
"May"</title>
<para><applicabil applicref="d"></applicabil> The word "shall" is
used to express a provision that is binding.  The words "should" and
"may" are used when it is necessary to express non-mandatory provisions.
 The word "will" may be used to express a mandatory declaration of
purpose or when it is necessary to express a future event.</para>
</para0>
<applicdef rtermwidth="5.5in" ltermwidth="2.0in" verstatus="ver"><title>List
of Applicability and Effectivity</title><para>In this example the
&ldquo;TERM&rdquo; heading is used to define the column used for the
symbol. The &ldquo;DEFINITION&rdquo; heading is used to define the
applicability/effectivity for the symbol used in the &ldquo;TERM&rdquo;
column.</para>
