</chapter><ipbchap security="u" sssn="23-00-00">
<ipbfwordchap security="u" sssn="23-00-00">
<para0 verstatus="ver"><title>This is The First Paragraph in the IPB</title>
<para>Some Organization use this first paragraph to explain what this <acronym>
<def>Illustrated Parts Breakdown</def><term>IPB</term></acronym> contains.
An example would be, &ldquo;This Illustrated Parts Breakdown contains
a list of all the parts necessary for the XXXX system.<prindex
pridnbr="2">Alpha primary entry</prindex></para>
</para0>
<ipbmodelcover applicref="a" verstatus="ver"><title> This Paragraph
Explains Which Models are Covered in the parts Breakdown</title><para>This
paragraph explains which models are covered in the parts breakdown.
A listing of the models, types, configurations, modifications, task
numbers, and series or blocks of the end item covered by the manual.<ftnote
id="ftnote-15"> This is a footnote in the IPB Chapter.</ftnote></para>
</ipbmodelcover>
<ipbfinding applicref="b"><title> Optional HOW to find Part Numbers,
Illustration, and Description</title><para>This is the place where
the usual two &ldquo;How to find&rdquo; graphics are inserted. Some
Organizations use a Para0 at the end of the IPB Foreword to insert
the &ldquo;How to&rdquo; graphics.</para>
</ipbfinding>
<ipbsimassem applicref="c"><title> Optional Listing of Similar Assemblies
</title><para>There are no similar assemblies in this <secindex
pridnbr="1">Illustrated Parts Breakdown</secindex>.</para>
</ipbsimassem>
<ipbquickchgexpl applicref="d"><title> Optional Quick Change Information</title>
<para>A table can be added to list the parts in a kit or quick change
unit.</para>
</ipbquickchgexpl>
<ipbshtnoexpl><title>Optional Explanation of the sheet number</title>
<para>This paragraph is used to explain the use of sheet numbers in
an Illustrated Parts Breakdown. If multiple sheet illustrations are
used, an explanation shall be included that the sheet number follows
the index number and is separated with a slash (/). The explanation
shall also state that, if an indexed item is on more than one sheet
of an illustration, the first and last sheet numbers on which the
item appears are given.</para>
</ipbshtnoexpl>
<ipbuseonexpl verstatus="ver"><title>This Paragraph Explains the Usable
on Codes</title><para>This paragraph explains the usable on Codes.
When breakdown of similar models are combined in the same IPB, part
variations within the models are indicated by a letter symbol in the
USABLE ON CODE column. Where the USABLE ON CODE column has been left
blank part listed applies to all models covered by this breakdown.</para>
</ipbuseonexpl>
<ipbsmrexpl verstatus="ver"><title>Source Maintenance and Recoverability
Code Explanation</title><para>This paragraph explains the <acronym><def>Source
Maintenance and Recoverability Code</def><term>SMR</term></acronym>.
This Manual contains Joint Military Services Uniform SMR codes. Source
and Repair Codes assigned by the Government and furnished by the procuring
activity. Definitions of these codes are available in TO 00-25-195.</para>
</ipbsmrexpl>
<ipbhcidesc><title>Optional Description for <acronym><def>Harness
Critical Item</def><term>HCI</term></acronym></title><para>This paragraph
would be use to explain the means of identifying Nuclear Harness Critical
Items. If HCI parts are listed in the Illustrated Parts Breakdown
the explanation would address the special requirements limiting changes
and substitutions, and that the specific part must be use to ensure
hardness is not degraded. </para>
</ipbhcidesc>
<ipbesdsdesc><title>Optional Explanation of<acronym><def>Electrostatic
Discharge Sensitive</def><term>ESDS</term></acronym></title><para>This
paragraph would be use to explain the identification of ESDS components
in the equipment covered by this Illustrated Parts Breakdown. There
will also be an explanation of the uniqueness and how to handle per
TO 00&ndash;25&ndash;234.</para>
</ipbesdsdesc>
<ipbpartstd verstatus="ver"><title>Part Standardization</title><para>This
paragraph explains Part Standardization. Authority for use of a part
number different than the part number  listed in this IPB is established
by the Department of Defense (DoD) Interchangeability and Substitution
Program. Refer to the DO43B Master Item Identification Base for Air
Force information. The maintenance technician has final responsibility
and authority for determining acceptability of substitute parts.</para>
</ipbpartstd>
<ipbmfrlist><title>Optional List of Manufactures</title><para>When
require by the acquiring activity a list of manufactures shall be
provided. The list shall contain the <acronym><def>Commercial and
Government Entity</def><term>CAGE</term></acronym> code and the name
and address of all manufactures whose CAGE codes are referenced in
the Parts List.</para>
</ipbmfrlist>
